      <title>1835 Nov. 21, Charlotte, Dixon C[oun]ty [to] Lot Hazard, Carthage, Tennessee / A[dam] Fergusson</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter to his father-in-law Lot Hazard from Adam Fergusson, dated November 21, 1835. Fergusson is reporting on a trip that he and his family are on. He writes that all are fine, but that it has been slow going due to heavy rains.</abstract>
